parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine compartment fires, resulting in vehicle damage or total loss.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine valve cover
engine compartment fires
vehicle stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling or Failure to Start
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or failure to start can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or fails to start
engine shuts off after driving a short distance
vehicle requires multiple repairs but still doesn't start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel turns excessively
the vehicle loses power
the wiring to the starter pops out
the vehicle dies
loss of all power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to retract can cause the seat belt to become tangled or stuck, making it difficult or impossible to use the seat belt properly, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract
the seat belt is stuck
the seat belt is tangled
the seat belt will not unlatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle weld can cause the rear axle to separate from the vehicle frame, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear axle becomes loose from the vehicle frame
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the vehicle pulls to one side
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear axle area.
